22/01/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the new Republika Srpska government were expected to take their posts Wednesday (22 January) at a formal ceremony in Banja Luka. The cabinet, led by Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic, represents the first multiethnic government to be elected in the Bosnian Serb entity.
In other news, the EU Police Mission announced Tuesday that it had made several arrests during raids Friday on nightclubs in Bosnia and Herzegovina. Some of the women who were detained proved to be victims of illegal trafficking. (OHR Sources - 22/01/03; RTRS, SRNA, BBC, PBS, Tanjug - 21/01/03)
